@startuml Helix Process Flow v2
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam activityBorderColor #2196F3
skinparam partitionBackgroundColor #F5F5F5
skinparam partitionBorderColor #9E9E9E
skinparam ArrowColor #424242
skinparam noteBorderColor #FFC107
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam padding 8
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

title **Helix: Idea ‚Üí Implementation-Ready Backlog (v2 - with Process Fixes)**

start

partition #FCE4EC "**PHASE 0: DISCOVERY** - Idea Refinement" {
  :Raw Startup Idea;

  :<<Agent>> **Idea Gatekeeper**
  Classify: VALID / NEEDS_CLARIFICATION / UNRELATED;

  if (Input Quality?) then (UNRELATED)
    #FF8A80:üõë **TERMINATE**
    ----
    Idea outside system scope;
    kill
  elseif (NEEDS_CLARIFICATION) then (NEEDS_CLARIFICATION)
    #FFF9C4:üë§ **Founder** answers questions;
    :<<Agent>> **Idea Refiner**
    Incorporate answers;
  else (VALID_IDEA)
    :<<Agent>> **Idea Polish**
    Grammar cleanup;
  endif

  :<<Agent>> **Idea Discovery**
  ----
  **Frameworks:** Lean Canvas, The Mom Test, JTBD
  ----
  Assess: Problem | Customer | UVP | Solution
  Coverage: clear / partial / missing;

  if (Gaps found?) then (Yes)
    #FFF9C4:üë§ **Founder** fills gaps
    (evidence-based);
  else (No gaps)
  endif

  :Refined Idea Statement;
}

partition #E3F2FD "**PHASE 1: WHY** - Idea Validation" {
  :<<Agent>> **Concept Expansion**
  ----
  **Frameworks:** Lean Canvas, Trigger-Based Problems, Pain Intensity
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ 3+ problems with trigger moments
  ‚Ä¢ Target users with budget indicators
  ‚Ä¢ Unique value proposition
  ‚Ä¢ Initial Lean Canvas;

  fork
    :<<Agent>> **Market Intelligence**
    ----
    **Framework:** Jobs-to-be-Done
    ----
    ‚Ä¢ Market size & trends
    ‚Ä¢ Core jobs (functional/emotional/social)
    ‚Ä¢ Current solutions vs workarounds;
  fork again
    :<<Agent>> **Competitor Analysis**
    ----
    **Framework:** Competitive Positioning
    ----
    ‚Ä¢ 5-7 real competitors
    ‚Ä¢ Feature gaps & sentiment
    ‚Ä¢ Switching cost analysis;
  end fork

  :<<Agent>> **Startup Validator**
  ----
  **Framework:** Claim Validation Matrix
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ 10-15 claims validated
  ‚Ä¢ Evidence: supported/partial/unsupported/contradicted
  ‚Ä¢ Risk level: HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW;

  if (Risk Level?) then (HIGH)
    :<<Agent>> **Pivot Strategy**
    ----
    ‚Ä¢ Alternative approaches
    ‚Ä¢ Scope adjustments;
    if (Viable Pivot?) then (No)
      #FF8A80:üõë **TERMINATE**
      ----
      No viable market path;
      kill
    else (Yes)
    endif
  else (MEDIUM/LOW)
  endif

  :<<Agent>> **Validation Summary**
  ----
  **Frameworks:** Lean Canvas (condensed), Six-Dimension Scoring
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ Executive summary
  ‚Ä¢ **GO / NO-GO / PIVOT** verdict
  ‚Ä¢ Next steps;
}

#FFF3E0:‚è∏ **GATE 1**
----
üë§ **Founder / CEO**
----
Is this opportunity worth pursuing?;

switch (Decision?)
case (NO-GO)
  #FF8A80:üõë **TERMINATE**
  ----
  Founder decision: not pursuing;
  kill
case (REVISE)
  #FFCDD2:‚Ü© **REVISE ‚Üí Phase 1**
  ----
  **Scope:** Re-run from
  Concept Expansion
  with founder feedback;
  stop
case (GO)
endswitch

partition #E8F5E9 "**PHASE 2: WHAT** - MVP Specification" {
  :<<Agent>> **MVP Scope**
  ----
  **Frameworks:** Shape Up, "The One Thing", Dependency Awareness
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ Core value proposition
  ‚Ä¢ Primary user segment
  ‚Ä¢ In/Out scope boundaries
  ‚Ä¢ Success criteria & failure signals
  ‚Ä¢ 2-3 core user flows;

  :<<Agent>> **Capability Model**
  ----
  **Framework:** Traceability Matrix
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ 3-5 functional capabilities
  ‚Ä¢ 2-4 non-functional capabilities
  ‚Ä¢ Each traces to user flows;

  :<<Agent>> **Scope Feasibility Check**
  ----
  **Framework:** Effort/Risk Matrix
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ Capability complexity assessment
  ‚Ä¢ Resource requirements
  ‚Ä¢ Feasibility: VIABLE / STRETCH / INFEASIBLE;

  if (Feasibility?) then (INFEASIBLE)
    if (Can reduce scope?) then (Yes)
      :<<Agent>> **Scope Pivot**
      ----
      ‚Ä¢ Reduce to core capabilities
      ‚Ä¢ Defer non-essential features;
    else (No)
      #FF8A80:üõë **TERMINATE**
      ----
      MVP not achievable
      with constraints;
      kill
    endif
  else (VIABLE/STRETCH)
  endif

  :<<Agent>> **System Traits**
  ----
  **Framework:** System Classification
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ Interface: web/CLI/API/IoT
  ‚Ä¢ Auth model
  ‚Ä¢ Deployment & data layer
  ‚Ä¢ Realtime needs;
}

#FFF3E0:‚è∏ **GATE 2**
----
üë§ **Product Owner / PM**
----
Is the scope focused and achievable?;

switch (Decision?)
case (REJECT)
  #FFCDD2:‚Ü© **REVISE ‚Üí MVP Scope**
  ----
  **Scope:** Revise MVP Scope
  or escalate to Gate 1;
  stop
case (APPROVE)
endswitch

partition #FBE9E7 "**PHASE 3: HOW** - Technical Design" {
  :<<Agent>> **Build vs Buy Analyzer**
  ----
  **Framework:** Technology Stack Segmentation
  ----
  Per capability:
  ‚Ä¢ BUILD / BUY / HYBRID
  ‚Ä¢ Effort & risk assessment;

  :<<Agent>> **Architecture Decisions**
  ----
  **Framework:** Architecture Decision Records (ADR)
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ Component structure
  ‚Ä¢ Technology stack
  ‚Ä¢ Integration patterns
  ‚Ä¢ DEC-* records;

  :<<Agent>> **Technical Feasibility Check**
  ----
  **Framework:** Constraint Analysis
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ Integration blockers
  ‚Ä¢ Technology constraints
  ‚Ä¢ Cost viability;

  if (Feasibility?) then (BLOCKED)
    #FFECB3:‚ö†Ô∏è **UPSTREAM ISSUE**
    ----
    Technical constraint
    invalidates Phase 2;

    if (Resolvable here?) then (No)
      #FFCDD2:‚Ü© **FEEDBACK ‚Üí Phase 2**
      ----
      **Cross-Phase:**
      Return with constraints;
      stop
    else (Yes)
      :<<Agent>> **Technical Pivot**
      ----
      ‚Ä¢ Alternative architecture
      ‚Ä¢ Adjusted build/buy;
    endif
  else (FEASIBLE)
  endif
}

#FFF3E0:‚è∏ **GATE 3**
----
üë§ **Solution Architect / Tech Lead**
----
Are the decisions technically sound?;

switch (Decision?)
case (REJECT-SCOPE)
  #FFCDD2:‚Ü© **ESCALATE ‚Üí Gate 2**
  ----
  **Scope:** Scope issue
  needs PO review;
  stop
case (REJECT-TECH)
  #FFCDD2:‚Ü© **REVISE ‚Üí Architecture**
  ----
  **Scope:** Fix architecture
  decisions only;
  stop
case (APPROVE)
endswitch

partition #F3E5F5 "**PHASE 4: STORIES** - Implementation Planning" {
  :<<Agent>> **Story Generation**
  ----
  **Frameworks:** Dependency-Layered Planning, Appetite-Bound
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ Stories per capability
  ‚Ä¢ BUILD ‚Üí implementation
  ‚Ä¢ BUY ‚Üí integration
  ‚Ä¢ Tagged: implements:CAP-*;

  :<<Agent>> **Story Validation**
  ----
  **Framework:** INVEST Criteria
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ Coverage verified
  ‚Ä¢ Quality validated
  ‚Ä¢ Gaps filled;

  :<<Agent>> **Dependency Ordering**
  ----
  **Framework:** Dependency Graph Resolution
  ----
  ‚Ä¢ Infrastructure ‚Üí Core ‚Üí Enhancements
  ‚Ä¢ Ready for sprint;
}

#C8E6C9:**OUTPUT**
====
üë§ **Handoff to: Dev Team Lead**
====
‚Ä¢ Validated business case
‚Ä¢ Locked MVP scope
‚Ä¢ Architecture decisions
‚Ä¢ Ordered user stories;

stop

